Package net.xqhs.util.logging

Class DumbLogger

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.xqhs.util.logging.BaseLogger
      • net.xqhs.util.logging.DumbLogger
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Logger, LoggerClassic
    public class DumbLogger
extends BaseLogger
    This class acts as a simple implementation for the LoggerClassic interface, not connected to any of the actual Logging infrastructure.

    A static instance is also offered, obtained by calling get().

    The intention for this class is that, should building a true logger fail, the class can use this implementation as a fall-back in order to simplify logging code.

    A 'preamble' is used for messages to mark the fact that they are printed out by this class. An alternative to the default preamble (#) can be given in the constructor.

    It prints all messages to the standard output. The only feature is that it assembles messages by replacing "\\[\\]" groups in the message with arguments received by methods (by calling Unit.compose(java.lang.String, java.lang.Object[]).

    Author:
    Andrei Olaru

      • lr

        public java.lang.Object lr​(java.lang.Object ret,
                           java.lang.String message,
                           java.lang.Object... arguments)
        Description copied from interface: Logger
        Outputs a fine logging message just before returning the Object in the argument.

        This method is supposed to be used in return statements, e.g. return lr(value, message);

        The Object in the argument is also put in the log message, in a form decided by the implementation.

        Specified by:
        lr in interface Logger
        Specified by:
        lr in class BaseLogger
        Parameters:
        ret - : the Object to return and to display.
        message - : the message to display beside the Object. Apparitions of the Logger.ARGUMENT_PLACEHOLDER will be replaced with instances in arguments, in the order in which they appear, by calling their Object.toString() method.
        arguments - : the arguments to be placed in the placeholders of the message string. Remaining arguments will be added after the message.
        Returns:
        the Object passed as argument.
